This paper deals with the problem of centralized coded caching and delivery in a radio access combination network (RACN), which involves the use of caches at both the edge nodes and the user equipments to reduce the delivery time. The network also involves wireless links and interference between the users. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories.
